This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, children in the Pacific benefit from an improved policy environment and evidence-based planning and financing.

description.narrative: The roll-out of Multiple Indicator Cluster Surveys (MICS) continued in 2021, with Samoa and Tuvalu launching their MICS reports, and Fiji completing the MICS survey. The new data will support the governments in their preparedness and response for the COVID-19 pandemic. The survey findings highlight the vulnerabilities of children to COVID-19 and are critical to informed decision-making by the government. MICS planning and preparation in the Federated States of Micronesia (FSM), Nauru, and Vanuatu, and preparation for an innovative ‘MICS Plus’ in Samoa were undertaken, with the surveys to be completed in 2022. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
